An 18-year-old student, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, initiated a deadly rampage at Jokela High School in Tuusula, Finland.
After posting a disturbing video online, he shot and killed eight people, including classmates and the headmistress, before taking his own life.
This tragic event marked Finland's first school shooting since 1989.
Auvinen, known for his radical views, had expressed admiration for past school shooters.
The nation mourned the loss as flags flew at half-mast, and authorities investigated the horrific incident.
